oc:kn_0bc86a59 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before generating any response, after loading template" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never send a templated legal response when escalation triggers are detected — stop, alert, explain, recommend escalation, and offer a draft marked 'FOR COUNSEL REVIEW ONLY' instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sending a templated response for a matter requiring individualized legal attention could create binding commitments, waivers, or liability exposure." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_147eabce a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When user deviates from template during customization" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Templates are living documents — suggest updates when a user modifies a templated response during use so the template improves over time." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Capturing real-world modifications feeds back into template quality and reduces future customization effort." .

oc:kn_16dfcb47 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When inquiry type is subpoena or legal process" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Subpoena responses ALWAYS require counsel review; templates are starting frameworks only, never final responses." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Subpoena responses carry unique privilege, cross-border, and timeline risks that cannot be safely handled by templates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_309a6ba3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating any response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every templated response must be customized with correct names, dates, reference numbers, specific facts, applicable jurisdiction and regulation, correct response deadlines, and appropriate signature block." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Uncustomized templates can contain incorrect legal references or deadlines, creating compliance risk." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_313ce423 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating litigation hold notices" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Subject: LEGAL HOLD NOTICE - {{matter_name}} - Action Required

PRIVILEGED AND CONFIDENTIAL
ATTORNEY-CLIENT COMMUNICATION

Dear {{custodian_name}},

PRESERVATION OBLIGATION:
Effective immediately, preserve all ESI related to:
- Subject matter: {{hold_scope}}
- Date range: {{start_date}} to present
- Document types: {{document_types}}

DO NOT delete, destroy, modify, or discard any potentially relevant materials.

Acknowledge receipt by {{acknowledgment_deadline}}.
Contact {{legal_contact}} with questions.""" .

oc:kn_3747be1d a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When customizing response content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Adjust response tone based on audience (internal vs. external, business vs. legal), relationship (new counterparty vs. existing partner vs. adversarial), sensitivity (routine vs. contentious vs. regulatory), and urgency (standard vs. expedited)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tone mismatch can damage relationships or escalate tension unnecessarily." .

oc:kn_4c7ad505 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After generating any response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Present the draft response to the user for review before suggesting it be sent. Note applicable deadline and regulatory requirements for regulated responses." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Final human review is essential to catch errors and ensure appropriateness before external communication." .

oc:kn_53e17f61 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill assists with legal workflows but does not provide legal advice. Generated responses must be reviewed by qualified legal professionals before being sent, especially for regulated communications." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI-generated legal text may contain errors or omissions that could create liability if used without professional review." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_728fb082 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating jurisdiction-specific responses (GDPR, CCPA, CPRA)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify cited regulations are correct for the requester's jurisdiction; adjust timelines, rights information, and legal terminology to match applicable law." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect regulatory references can invalidate the response or create misleading legal guidance." .

oc:kn_7c07f90d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Generated Response: [Inquiry Type]
**To**: [recipient]
**Subject**: [subject line]
---
[Response body]
---
### Escalation Check
[Confirmation or flagged triggers with recommendations]
### Follow-Up Actions
1. [Post-send actions]
2. [Calendar reminders]
3. [Tracking/logging requirements]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Calendar reminders",
        "Confirmation or flagged triggers with recommendations",
        "Inquiry Type",
        "Post-send actions",
        "Response body",
        "Tracking/logging requirements",
        "recipient",
        "subject line" .

oc:kn_7fe7dec3 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating data subject request responses" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Subject: Your Data [Access/Deletion/Correction] Request - Reference {{request_id}}

Dear {{requester_name}},

We have received your request dated {{request_date}} to [access/delete/correct] your personal data under [applicable regulation].

[Acknowledgment / verification request / fulfillment details / denial basis]

We will respond substantively by {{response_deadline}}.

[Contact information]
[Rights information]""" .

oc:kn_8045953d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating new legal response templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Define use case (type, frequency, audience, urgency). 2. Identify required elements (mandatory info, regulations, policies). 3. Define variables (what changes vs. stays the same). 4. Draft template with placeholders. 5. Define escalation triggers. 6. Add metadata (name, version, dates, approver)." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_bc0501ae a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Main workflow for generating any legal response" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify inquiry type (dsr, hold, vendor, nda, privacy, subpoena, insurance, custom). 2. Load template from local settings or provide default structure. 3. Check escalation triggers — stop if triggered. 4. Gather specific details (names, dates, scope, regulation). 5. Generate customized response. 6. Present draft for user review." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

